    %p
      Hybrid Bills mix the characteristics of
      = link_to 'Public Bills', 'http://www.parliament.uk/about/how/laws/bills/public/', target: '_blank'
      %span.sr-only
        This link will open in a new window
      and
      = link_to 'Private Bills', 'http://www.parliament.uk/about/how/laws/bills/private/', target: '_blank'
      %span.sr-only
        This link will open in a new window
      \. They often propose works of national importance in a specific area of the UK.

    %p For example, the Channel Tunnel Bills passed in the 1970s and 1980s and the Crossrail Bill passed in 2008.

    %p Changes to the law proposed by a Hybrid Bill affect the general public and impact specific individuals, groups or organisations.

    %p
